[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{When the opponents interfere, Jacoby is off. Now a cue-bid response by partner shows a hand with good trump support, and a limit raise or better in strength. So partner might have a game forcing hand, but also might have only 11 points.

But he definitely has \S support. You show your minimum hand by bidding 3\S and he passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:765.AJT96.KQ.A65 QT83.73.J863.KQT K.KQ85.A972.J743 AJ942.42.T54.982"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H pass 2NT pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "9aeb631d981a3fb456acf131eb063d4617f0007beaab7063c10221658a10ae81"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{Click back to Deal 12 for a quick comparison between the two hands. Almost identical, but this time your singleton is the \SK. Since it is not advisable to Splinter with a singleton Ace, King or Queen you just bid 2NT instead. Partner jumps to 4\H and you pass.

Note that in this hand the three points you credited for your \SK are completely wasted. And although partner has the same hand as he did in Deal 12, this time there is no chance of making slam. This shows why you don't Splinter with singleton Honors.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:3.KQ753.KQJ6.A86 864.84.AT2.QJT52 KQJ52.AJT2.954.7 AT97.96.873.K943"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "5H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1H pass 4C pass 4NT pass 5D pass 5H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "4f51a6b0b6b4418986629d57a003449b6b7aaf3e04d5eb0f2dbad89ad24e7bfa"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{When partner Splinters his singleton \C you should realize that the only thing that could keep you from making slam would be lack of Aces. So you bid 4NT. Partner shows only one Ace so you just sign off at 5\H.}

