[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "94ec3722b13b3fa29a78e9ea945e10babd0e822795048448cd2fbfd94ec19982"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{When partner opens 1\S you have a pretty normal Jacoby 2NT response. He next says 3\S.  

Your partner has a better than minimum hand with 6 \Ss. However, you have an average hand with no controls to show so you use the Principle of Fast Arrival and bid 4\S. Everyone passes.}

